  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed amendment, to allow the proposed scheme to be phased through the introduction of Phases 0-3, would have a material impact on the approved application, likely leading to a delay in both the delivery of housing from this site and the delivery of social infrastructure (through CIL and s106 payments) which is required to mitigate the harm arising from the development. As such, the application would be contrary to  Policy CI1 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Strategic Policies (2012) Policy DMCI 7 of the Hillingdon Local Plan: Development Management Policies (2020) and Policy DF1 of the London Plan (2021), and is therefore refused under s96a of the Town and Country Planning Act (1990)."
